You need to update your `useEffect` dependency array so it references the current value of `auto` rather than the one from the previous render. You also need to call `clearTimeout` if necessary on the previous timer when the effect is re-run, and it&#39;s usually a good idea to return a clean-up function if your component gets un-mounted to avoid memory leaks.

    const timerRef = useRef(null)

    useEffect(() =&gt; {
        if(timerRef.current){
            clearTimeout(timerRef.current);
        }
        timerRef.current = setTimeout(() =&gt; {
            if (auto) {
                setCurrent(c=&gt;c+1);
            }
        }, 5000);
        return ()=&gt;clearTimeout(timerRef.current);
    }, [auto, current]);

